JOHANNESBURG A possible bidding war for South Africa s biggest cement maker may soon get underway.Dangote Cement has officially approached PPC cement about a possible takeover.The Nigeria-based company, owned by billionaire Aliko Dangote, told PPC s board of its interest to purchase its entire share capital.READ: Dangote Industries to buy over 65% of Tiger Brands Nigeria for $1This follows an earlier joint offer led by Canada s Fairfax Financial Holdings and South African firm AfriSam.If Dangote Cement s bid is successful, the merger will combine two of Africa s largest cement makers, leading to continent wide operations.eNCA